<p>You make some interesting points about the prose and font use. I suppose in terms of the font, it's a toss-up between authenticity versus readability, and you can't fully have both! I hope this issue doesn't deter any readers.</p>
<p>On another note, I'd like to point out that the article is more than just the three letters by O'Sullivan &#8212; in fact, it's another <em>three (3)</em> ListPages following that (some of which use other custom fonts), as linked in the page navigation at the bottom. This feedback has made me realize that the ListPages aren't too explicit; so, I've added an out-of-universe note to the top of each page in the article. There's a lot of additional context that tells a broader story than just the letters. Hope that helps!</p>

