			<div class="content" id="post-content-4291719">
									

<p>Yeah another user had suggested that too for the second listpage though me and my partner are busy and cant go back to condense the right parts. Will definitely keep this in mind, thank you for your extensive feedback.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">O'Sullivan</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>I remember when we were young, we would read the posters and poems and newspapers from Father's small print shop. She was always frail and soft-spoken.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Perhaps I played up his wage work more than what was necessary but I had this sense that like many immigrants of the time, they only had what they could find as laborers primarily. Jobs that they might have not specialized in back home. Like a college graduate in literature working a McDonald's job.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I do question why 8 (+ 1) women were sacrificed by fifthists however; why not 5? I may have missed a trick here.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>A) the photo had 9, and I couldn't find a decent one of 5 women for whatever reason but also;<br />
B) <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nine_maidens_(mythology)#Ireland">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nine_maidens_(mythology)#Ireland</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muses">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muses</a> &lt;- had it in mind to loosely reference these mythologies given its almost like &quot;magick&quot;, from all parts of the world, comes to America.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

